            <title>[CAMEL-21770] camel-kubernetes: Autowired KubernetesClient should not be closed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-21770</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a problem with context reloading triggered from k8s secrets when using an autowired KubernetesClient.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Both SecretsReloadTriggerTask and AbstractKubernetesEndpoint close the KubernetesClient. When routes get refreshed, the closed client is wired back in an unusable state.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
